data.description:
A private one-acre lot with much potential awaits you in the ever-growing Walton County. If you want to live privately in the woods but not too deep in the woods, this is your spot! Come home to a well-maintained 4 bedroom, 2 bath double wide mobile home with a storage shed and fun recreational courses already built on the property. This could be a spot for your full-time residence, a second home getaway close to the beach but out of the traffic, or allow the mobile home to be your temporary shelter as you build a forever home on this entire X-Zoned Floodplain One-Acre parcel.  This home has a split floor plan with a living room and fireplace den. The primary bedroom is extra-large at 21.8x12.5 dimensions with a primary bathroom ensuite. The ensuite includes a double vanity and a separate oversized tub and shower, while the three guest bedrooms are on the other side of the home. All guest bedrooms have walk-in closets and share a shower/tub combo bathroom. A kitchen/dining area has a laundry room and storage hidden behind the kitchen pantry doors.  

South County Highway 183 is less than a 10-minute drive to Morrison Springs, a 20-minute drive to Defuniak Springs, a 30-minute drive to Freeport, and a 45-minute drive to Grayton Beach on Scenic Highway 30A. This is a wonderful opportunity to live in a quiet community close to it all.
